No surprise here.

250
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:43,791
You guys went with
the same one I did.

251
00:12:43,875 --> 00:12:46,208
The first choice is a
tried and true classic,

252
00:12:46,291 --> 00:12:48,166
but it doesn't apply
in the situation.

253
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:50,083
And it does sound
a little cliché.

254
00:12:50,166 --> 00:12:51,833
Option two is also out.

255
00:12:51,916 --> 00:12:54,541
If he escapes, he can't
continue the conversation.

256
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:55,666
Number three it is.

257
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:56,875
I agree.

258
00:12:56,958 --> 00:12:58,791
In this case, three
makes the most sense.

259
00:12:58,875 --> 00:13:01,000
She'll let him live and
he'll get to know her better.

260
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:03,166
'Kay, Shido, we've
made up your mind!

261
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,625
Now listen closely and
then repeat after me.

262
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:07,125
[PRINCESS]
What are you waiting for?

263
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:10,583
Answer the question already!

264
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,666
Before asking for
someone's name,

265
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:15,083
you should really
give your own first!

266
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,916
I hate you, Kotori!

267
00:13:18,958 --> 00:13:20,666
[KOTORI] Well,
that was unexpected!

268
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:23,958
Unexpected my ass,
I could've been dead!

269
00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:25,541
No more time for games.

270
00:13:25,625 --> 00:13:26,625
If you do not answer me,

271
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,750
I can only assume
you are my enemy.

272
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:30,333
[SHIDO]
My name is Shido Itsuka.

273
00:13:30,416 --> 00:13:34,958
I'm a student at this school.
I've got no reason to fight you.

274
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:36,250
Hold on.

275
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:37,958
This isn't the first time
we've crossed paths.

276
00:13:38,041 --> 00:13:39,125
No, it's not.

277
00:13:39,208 --> 00:13:41,500
I saw you on the
tenth in the city.

278
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:43,500
That's right. I thought so.

279
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:46,833
I remember you saying
something odd to me that day.

280
00:13:46,916 --> 00:13:48,208
[SHIDO winces]

281
00:13:48,291 --> 00:13:49,750
You said you didn't
come to kill me,

282
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:51,375
and that you couldn't
kill anyone.

283
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:56,791
And now I know that was a lie.
Why else would you be here?

284
00:13:56,875 --> 00:14:01,291
Your face. How come
you always look so sad?

285
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:03,166
I'm not trying to do anything.

286
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:06,291
And it's true. I really
have no reason to kill you.

287
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:07,625
[PRINCESS] Quit lying!

288
00:14:07,708 --> 00:14:09,375
Every single human
is out to get me.

289
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:11,750
I haven't done a thing to
them yet they want me dead.

290
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,958
I swear, that's not true!

291
00:14:14,041 --> 00:14:15,708
You never answered me.

292
00:14:15,791 --> 00:14:18,458
You claim to have no
intention of killing anyone.

293
00:14:18,541 --> 00:14:22,208
If that's really the truth,
tell my why it is you came here.

294
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,500
Her first reaction
wasn't all that pretty.

295
00:14:25,583 --> 00:14:28,166
This time, option one's
probably the safest choice.

296
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:30,125
[SHIDO]
I-- I wanted to meet you!

297
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:31,750
To meet me?

298
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:33,500
Why would you want that?

299
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:38,083
[KOTORI]
Do you guys have any ideas?

300
00:14:38,166 --> 00:14:39,833
[KAWAGOE] I recommend a
straightforward approach.

301
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:41,166
[NAKATSUGAWA]
Yeah, be clear and direct!

302
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:43,541
This girl's way too dense
to get anything subtle.

303
00:14:43,625 --> 00:14:45,000
[KOTORI]
That's a good point.

304
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:46,333
We've already wasted enough time

305
00:14:46,416 --> 00:14:48,541
answering all of
these questions.

306
00:14:48,625 --> 00:14:50,000
Um. It's simple.

307
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:52,458
I came here because
I'm interested in you.

308
00:14:56,291 --> 00:14:58,291
I'm in no mood to joke around.

309
00:14:58,375 --> 00:15:00,875
I know, and neither am I.

310
00:15:04,083 --> 00:15:05,250
You want to know the truth?

311
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:08,250
I came here so I
could talk to you.

312
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:10,416
I don't even care
what we talk about.

313
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:11,708
Not one bit!

314
00:15:11,791 --> 00:15:15,208
You can ignore me
if you want to!

315
00:15:15,291 --> 00:15:19,416
But know this, I'm not
like every other human.

316
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:20,541
Because--

317
00:15:20,625 --> 00:15:21,750
[KOTORI] Stop it,
wait for our signal!

318
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:23,750
Because I'll never
let you down!

319
00:15:28,166 --> 00:15:30,458
[PRINCESS] You said your
name was Shido, right?

320
00:15:30,541 --> 00:15:32,375
And when you said you
were interested in me,

321
00:15:32,458 --> 00:15:34,041
were you being serious?

322
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:35,666
[SHIDO]
Yes, I was.

323
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,375
But like
serious serious?

324
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:39,291
[SHIDO]
Serious serious.

325
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:42,041
[PRINCESS] One-hundred
percent serious serious?

326
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:45,666
[SHIDO] One-thousand
percent serious serious!

327
00:15:47,916 --> 00:15:49,083
Jerk!

328
00:15:49,166 --> 00:15:51,333
Who would seriously fall
for your amateur tricks?

329
00:15:51,416 --> 00:15:52,750
Stupid, dummy!

330
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:53,833
But that was
from the heart!

331
00:15:53,916 --> 00:15:56,166
Then again, this is different.

332
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:58,833
I still don't know what
your intentions are.

333
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,833
But you are the only
human I've ever had

334
00:16:00,916 --> 00:16:03,166
a normal conversation with.

335
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:05,583
You know this world,
which could serve me well.

336
00:16:05,666 --> 00:16:07,166
It might just work.

337
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:08,666
Yep, it's settled.

338
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:10,666
This should prove
your usefulness.

339
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:11,791
Uh, thanks I guess.

340
00:16:11,875 --> 00:16:14,041
Um. Oh yeah, what was
your name again?

341
00:16:14,125 --> 00:16:17,000
My name? I've never
had one of those.

342
00:16:17,083 --> 00:16:19,125
But I suppose I will need
one if I want to find out

343
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:21,333
why humans are so awful.

344
00:16:21,416 --> 00:16:24,375
Okay. Why don't you come up
with something you can call me?

345
00:16:24,458 --> 00:16:27,250
Well she's certainly putting
the Fraxinus to work, isn't she?

346
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:30,375
All right crew, we need to
think of a name, on the double!

347
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:36,083
The few suggestions we have
aren't gonna be enough.

348
00:16:36,166 --> 00:16:38,375
Do you want to call in the
troops from around the world?

349
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:40,000
One step ahead of you!

350
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:44,208
[phone beeps]

351
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:46,708
Gosh, now what does she want?

352
00:16:50,958 --> 00:16:52,083
Heh, heh, heh.

353
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:54,625
Your wish is my command,
my digital darling!

354
00:16:54,708 --> 00:16:56,166
Isn't that that
fool Tonomachi?

355
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:58,666
He's probably sending
a dirty text to Shido!

356
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,666
That's so lame.

357
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,666
Come on man, we're
not naming Princess

358
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:13,250
after one of your ex-wives!

359
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:15,125
I don't even know how to
pronounce that gibberish!

360
00:17:15,208 --> 00:17:16,250
[MIKIMOTO]
It's Clare-ah-bell.

361
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,750
[KOTORI]
The nineteen twenties are over!

362
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:21,666
Can't anyone here think of
a halfway decent girl's name?

363
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,000
What about Tome?

364
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:24,041
Tome!

365
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:26,875
Tome sounds kinda neat, right?

366
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:31,791
Wow, she's mad.
Was Tome that bad?

367
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:35,166
Don't think I can't
tell when a human

368
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:37,416
is attempting to make
fun of me. You got it?

369
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,291
[SHIDO]
Okay, just a minute!

370
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:40,875
Apologies to anyone named Tome,

371
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:42,500
but I don't think
I know a single girl

372
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:43,958
that would like that name.

373
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:45,541
Think, Shido!

374
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:49,166
There has to be a
perfect name for her!

375
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:52,291
How about Tohka?

376
00:17:52,375 --> 00:17:55,458
Tohka. Yeah,
I guess that'll work.

377
00:17:58,125 --> 00:17:59,541
Is this how it's written?

378
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:00,791
It is.

379
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:05,833
[TOHKA] Huh...

380
00:18:05,916 --> 00:18:07,166
Tohka.

381
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,916
Now I have a name!

382
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,416
I think I like it.

383
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,375
Thank you.

384
00:18:12,458 --> 00:18:14,666
Yeah. Yeah, you're welcome.

385
00:18:17,375 --> 00:18:20,000
Tohka just means "tenth,"
as in the day we met.

386
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:22,708
But hey, it's not like
she'll ever need to know that.

387
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:24,208
Get down and take cover!

388
00:18:24,291 --> 00:18:29,083
[gunfire]

389
00:18:29,166 --> 00:18:31,000
[AST GIRL 2-1] Are you sure
this is okay, Captain?

390
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:32,875
[RYOKO] We have permission
to smoke them out.

391
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:34,125
Once we've done our job,

392
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:36,250
the reinforcements can
take care of the rest.

393
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:39,625
[SHIDO]
Are you all right?

394
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:41,666
Hurry up and leave
while you still can.

395
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,000
I'd love to continue our talk,

396
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:45,708
but the last thing I want
is for you to get hurt.

397
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:48,791
Don't just stand there.
Get going before they open fire!

398
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:50,416
I'm staying right here!

399
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:55,333
Sit down. I wanna
talk some more!

400
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:57,166
You want to know about
this world, don't you?

401
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:58,500
So have a seat!

402
00:18:58,583 --> 00:19:00,500
Pretend they're not even there!

403
00:19:00,583 --> 00:19:02,000
[TOHKA] Alright.

404
00:19:02,583 --> 00:19:15,208
[gunfire]

405
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:16,416
[SHIDO]
I'm curious.

406
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:18,958
If you're not human,
what exactly are you?

407
00:19:19,041 --> 00:19:20,291
[TOHKA]
I don't know.

408
00:19:20,375 --> 00:19:21,916
I don't remember
how long ago it was

409
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,041
when I appeared out of nowhere.

410
00:19:24,125 --> 00:19:25,666
That's all I can recall.

411
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:28,750
Most of my oldest memories
are fuzzy and distorted.

412
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:31,208
I honestly don't know
what kind of being I am.

413
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:32,333
[SHIDO]
That's awful!

414
00:19:32,416 --> 00:19:33,791
[TOHKA]
I suppose so.

415
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:35,875
My birth was sudden
and inexplicable,

416
00:19:35,958 --> 00:19:38,791
and the Mecha-Mecha Squad was
already in the air when I awoke.

417
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:39,916
[SHIDO]
Mecha-Mecha huh?

418
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,458
[TOHKA] Them.
The noisy flying people.

419
00:19:42,541 --> 00:19:43,833
[SHIDO] Interesting.

420
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:45,291
[KOTORI]
Here's your chance!

421
00:19:45,375 --> 00:19:47,750
Her happiness meter
is over seventy.

422
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:50,250
Now's as good a time
as any to make a move.

423
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:51,708
[SHIDO]
What do you want me to do?

424
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:53,791
[KOTORI] For starters you
could ask her out on a date.

425
00:19:53,875 --> 00:19:54,625
Uh...!

426
00:19:54,708 --> 00:19:56,625
[TOHKA]
Hm? What's wrong?

427
00:19:56,708 --> 00:19:58,125
Uh, nothing,
I'm just itchy.

428
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:00,666
You've been muttering under
your breath for a while.

429
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,500
Are you hiding
something from me?

430
00:20:02,583 --> 00:20:04,041
[SHIDO] No, no,
you're overreacting!

431
00:20:04,125 --> 00:20:05,916
Then tell me what you
were saying just now.

432
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,375
[SHIDO] I... forgot?

433
00:20:07,458 --> 00:20:10,416
Come on. Cut to the
chase and ask her out.

434
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,041
Ask her out! Ask her out!

435
00:20:12,125 --> 00:20:14,583
[GROUP] Ask her out!
Ask her out! Ask her out!

436
00:20:14,666 --> 00:20:18,166
Ask her out! Ask her out!
Ask her out! Ask her out!

437
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:21,291
All right already!
Shut up! I'll do it!

438
00:20:21,375 --> 00:20:23,458
Tohka, I wanna
ask you something.

439
00:20:23,541 --> 00:20:26,333
Um but it's-- Well,
it's kind of abrupt.

440
00:20:26,416 --> 00:20:28,125
But, will you go out
on a date with me?

441
00:20:28,208 --> 00:20:29,291
[gunfire]

442
00:20:29,375 --> 00:20:31,666
Have we received any
new orders, Origami?

443
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:33,000
That's a negative, ma'am.

444
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:34,708
[RYOKO]
Even after all this?

445
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:37,041
Wait a minute.

446
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:39,250
Someone is down there
with the Spirit!

447
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:41,375
Hold on; hold your fire!

448
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:44,583
[gasps]

449
00:20:47,625 --> 00:20:49,916
[RYOKO]
Origami, get back here!

450
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,041
What exactly is a date?

451
00:20:52,125 --> 00:20:52,875
[SHIDO]
You don't know?

452
00:20:52,958 --> 00:20:54,458
[KOTORI]
Look out! The AST!

453
00:20:54,541 --> 00:20:55,916
Ahh!

454
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,083
[TOHKA]
How rude!

455
00:20:58,166 --> 00:20:59,291
What? Tobiichi?

456
00:20:59,375 --> 00:21:00,333
Stand back.

457
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:02,208
Well, if it isn't you again.

458
00:21:02,291 --> 00:21:05,041
He's not your shield, you scum.

459
00:21:05,125 --> 00:21:06,291
[SHIDO]
You've got it all wrong!

460
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:07,875
[RYOKO]
What are you doing, Origami?

461
00:21:07,958 --> 00:21:10,750
We don't have orders
to break in on foot!

462
00:21:11,791 --> 00:21:13,291
[TOHKA]
Sandalphon!

463
00:21:17,625 --> 00:21:19,458
[KOTORI]
Shido, get out of there now!

464
00:21:19,541 --> 00:21:21,541
The Fraxinus will
come to retrieve you.

465
00:21:21,625 --> 00:21:23,375
And leave her here alone?

466
00:21:28,541 --> 00:21:30,125
[ORIGAMI yells]

467
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,416
[helicopter sound]

468
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:37,208
[RYOKO] You could have
been killed out there!

469
00:21:37,291 --> 00:21:40,791
Do you realize just how lucky
you are she became Lost?

470
00:21:43,666 --> 00:21:46,166
Exercise some restraint. Okay?

471
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:48,125
You're a valuable
member of the AST.

472
00:21:48,208 --> 00:21:49,958
So start acting like it!

473
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:59,208
[SHIDO] I was there
when everything happened.

474
00:21:59,291 --> 00:22:04,000
Still, the massive destruction
just doesn't seem real.

475
00:22:04,083 --> 00:22:07,750
But yesterday was real.

476
00:22:07,833 --> 00:22:09,958
It wasn't a dream at all.

477
00:22:10,041 --> 00:22:11,000
[TOHKA] Shido!

478
00:22:11,083 --> 00:22:12,333
[SHIDO]
That's right.

479
00:22:12,416 --> 00:22:15,000
I really did talk with
Tohka and give her a name.

480
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,750
--Crazy.
--Hey, Shido!

481
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:18,875
[TOHKA]
Quit ignoring me!

482
00:22:20,625 --> 00:22:21,708
[SHIDO] Tohka!

483
00:22:21,791 --> 00:22:23,583
You just now noticed me?

484
00:22:23,666 --> 00:22:25,666
Wow, you are so dumb!

485
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:28,208
But how did you end
up back over here?

486
00:22:28,291 --> 00:22:29,958
The spatial alarm
didn't even go off!

487
00:22:30,041 --> 00:22:31,000
[TOHKA]
Why would it?

488
00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:33,125
You were the one
who invited me back.

489
00:22:33,208 --> 00:22:35,500
For a date I think?

490
00:22:35,583 --> 00:22:37,791
Well guess what?
It's time for that date!

491
00:22:37,875 --> 00:22:40,791
Let's go, let's go, let's go,
let's go, let's go, let's go!

492
00:22:40,875 --> 00:22:42,583
Okay! Just bring
it down a bit!

493
00:22:42,666 --> 00:22:44,750
And you should probably
get out of that first.

494
00:22:44,833 --> 00:22:46,166
Do you mind changing?

495
00:22:46,250 --> 00:22:48,625
Right now? You want me to
undress in broad daylight?

496
00:22:48,708 --> 00:22:51,125
No, that's not it!

497
00:22:51,208 --> 00:22:52,791
Lemme show
you an example.

498
00:22:54,416 --> 00:22:56,500
